Softcover. Condition: Good. First Edition. A nostalgic look at the last major railroad to use steam locomotives, long after others had given up. Follows the remarkable history of Norfolk & Western steam engines as they hauled coal through the mountains of West Virginia and Virginia. Includes dramatic photos from one of the last steam-operated rail lines in the country. Seller Inventory # SONG0890243166
